wikipedia_page.main: Edward Fairfax Taylor (10 July 1845 – 27 January 1902) was an English first-class cricketer active 1865–67 who played for Surrey. He was born in Holborn; died in Ewell.

response: Edward Taylor (c. 1642–1729) was a colonial American poet, physician, and pastor.

* Edward Taylor (music writer) (1784–1863), English singer, writer on music, and Gresham Professor of Music
